qas.question: What English phrase does I ❤ NY represent?
When was I ❤ NY first used in advertisements?
Who owns the trademark to I ❤ NY?

answers.text: New York State Empire State Development

qas.question: What is the state song of New York?
I Love New York was established as advertising in what year?
What is the state song of New York?

context: <a0_0><a3_0><a5_0>I Love New York<a5_0/><a3_0/><a0_0/> (stylized I ❤ NY) is both a logo and a song that are the basis of an advertising campaign and have been used since <a1_0><a4_0>1977<a4_0/><a1_0/> to promote tourism in New York City, and later to promote New York State as well. The trademarked logo, owned by <a2_0>New York State Empire State Development<a2_0/>, appears in souvenir shops and brochures throughout the city and state, some licensed, many not. The song is the state song of New York.
